<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 31 at 8:50PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>... LOCALLY DENSE FOG LIKELY OVERNIGHT...
Locally dense fog has developed across much of southern New
England. Widespread visibility reductions to between 1/2 and 3
miles are already occurring or are are expected to develop
shortly. Visibilities may drop below 1/4 mile at times.
If you encounter fog while driving, proceed with extra caution.
remember to reduce speed, use low beam headlights, and keep extra
space between vehicles.</description>
